s_eligible` contract in `role_gate.py`. Each rule (MetricAccent, PhraseArch, Agogic, DurationContrast, FinalRit, Punctuation, Articulation, Microtiming) has been updated to check `applies_to(role, metadata)` before performing any mutations. The machine identity preservation requirement is satisfied by ensuring `bootstrap_identity()` is called before `FirstBootAnnouncer` in both daemon entry points (`daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py`).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAll R1–R8 rules are covered. Integration and gate tests in `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py` exhaustively verify that melodic roles are shaped while grid-locked roles (like `ostinato`) remain exactly quantized and unmutated. Identity persistence is verified by `tests/test_first_boot.py`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe shared contract follows established patterns in the render pipeline. Rule IDs (R1–R8) are consistently applied and mapped to their respective implementations. The use of `role_is_eligible` provides a single point of truth for gating logic.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nNo security vulnerabilities or leaked secrets were found. Identity preservation follows the existing file-based persistence model.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe code is well-structured and follows the project's architectural standards. The integration tests provide high confidence in the behavioral correctness of the gating mechanism.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- None.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\